Program: Start the Week
Title: History of Music - John Adams and Howard Goodall
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01pz9xn
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 21 Jan 2013
On Start the Week, Tom Sutcliffe talks to Howard Goodall about 40,000 years of music, from prehistoric instruments to modern-day pop, to chart a history of innovation and entertainment. The composer John Adams contrasts European and American traditions as he conducts two concerts at the LSO. The award-winning writer Stephen Poliakoff brings the true story of a black British jazz band in the 1930s to the small screen. And Barb Jungr's cd of cover versions harks back to a tradition of musical re-interpretation. Producer: Katy Hickman. Show less